LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
Moved by Monks
Seconded by Tanner(14)
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE AMENDMENT TO S.B. NO. 1142
1 AMENDMENT TO THE BILL
2 On page 1 of the printed bill, following line 22, insert:
3 "SECTION 6. That Section 33-1031, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
4 amended to read as follows:
5 33-1031. EMPOWERING PARENTS GRANT PROGRAM. (1) There is hereby estab-
6 lished the empowering parents grant program, to be administered by the board
7 according to the provisions of this section. The purpose of the program is to
8 provide education grants for eligible students.
9 (2) In order to administer the program, the board:
10 (a) Shall create and administer, or designate a third party to create
11 and administer, a grant distribution platform;
12 (b) Shall establish a grant application process for parents;
13 (c) Shall establish provisions for the reimbursement of any eligi-
14 ble education expense for which reimbursement is required and di-
15 rect payment from the platform is not permitted pursuant to section
16 33-1030(3)(a), Idaho Code;
17 (d) Shall, subject to appropriation, award grants. Grant awards shall
18 be made in the following order of preference:
19 (i) First to eligible students whose household has an adjusted
20 gross income under sixty thousand dollars ($60,000), as verified
21 by the Idaho state tax commission using the prior year's tax re-
22 turns. Notification of grant awards for students in this category
23 shall be made within thirty (30) days of application, and grant
24 funds shall be made available for participants' use as soon as
25 practicable, but no later than thirty (30) days after the notifi-
26 cation of a grant award;
27 (ii) Starting sixty (60) days after grant awards in a fiscal year
28 are made under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, to eligible
29 students whose household has an adjusted gross income under sev-
30 enty-five thousand dollars ($75,000), as verified by the Idaho
31 state tax commission using the prior year's tax returns; and
32 (iii) Starting sixty (60) days after grant awards in a fiscal year
33 are made under subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph, to all other
34 eligible students on a first-come, first-served basis until all
35 available funds are distributed; and
36 (e) May take such other actions as are necessary to implement and en-
37 force the provisions of this section.
38 (3) Prior to the award of a grant, the parent of a participant shall
39 agree to verify program compliance. The parent of a participant shall use

2
1 grant funds only for eligible education expenses. If a parent is found to
2 misuse grant funds, then neither the parent nor another parent of the student
3 living in the same household may apply for a grant in the future for any stu-
4 dent, provided that the parent may appeal the finding to the board.
5 (4) Grant funds shall be expended within three (3) years after they
6 are awarded. Any unused funds at the end of the three (3) year period shall
7 revert to the empowering parents grant program fund established in section
8 33-1034, Idaho Code. At any time before the three (3) year period ends, un-
9 used funds may be forfeited and transferred from the participant account to
10 the program fund.
11 (5) Grant awards per family shall be capped at three thousand dollars
12 ($3,000), regardless of the number of eligible students in the family.
13 (6) No grant awards shall be made under the provisions of this section
14 on or after the effective date of this act. Any grants awarded prior to the
15 effective date of this act may be used as provided in this section.";
16 and renumber subsequent sections accordingly.
17 AMENDMENT TO SECTION 6
18 On page 1, delete lines 36 and 37.
19 On page 2, delete lines 1 and 2, and insert:
20 "(2) On June 20, 2028, and by no later than June 30, 2028, the state con-
21 troller shall transfer the unobligated cash balance remaining in the empow-
22 ering parents grant program fund into the general fund.".
23 AMENDMENT TO SECTION 8
24 On page 2, delete lines 6 through 8, and insert: "declared to exist, Sec-
25 tions 6 and 7 of this act shall be in full force and effect on and after pas-
26 sage and approval, and Sections 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 8 of this act shall be in
27 full force and effect on and after July 1, 2028.".
28 CORRECTION TO TITLE
29 On page 1, in line 8, following "EVALUATION;" insert: "AMENDING SECTION
30 33-1031, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE FOR THE TERMINATION OF GRANT AWARDS;"; and in
31 line 11, delete "AN EFFECTIVE DATE" and insert: "EFFECTIVE DATES".

